{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"The key question is, \"When are we going to get fusion?\""},{"time":5000,"text":"It's really been a long time since we've known about fusion."},{"time":8000,"text":"We've known about fusion since 1920,"},{"time":10000,"text":"when Sir Arthur Stanley Eddington"},{"time":12000,"text":"and the British Association for the Advancement of Science"},{"time":15000,"text":"conjectured that that's why the sun shines."}]},{"cues":[{"time":18000,"text":"I've always been very worried about resource."},{"time":21000,"text":"I don't know about you, but"},{"time":23000,"text":"when my mother gave me food,"},{"time":25000,"text":"I always sorted the ones I disliked"},{"time":28000,"text":"from the ones I liked."},{"time":30000,"text":"And I ate the disliked ones first,"},{"time":32000,"text":"because the ones you like, you want to save."},{"time":36000,"text":"And as a child you're always worried about resource."},{"time":39000,"text":"And once it was sort of explained to me"},{"time":42000,"text":"how fast we were using up the world's resources,"},{"time":46000,"text":"I got very upset,"},{"time":48000,"text":"about as upset as I did when I realized"},{"time":50000,"text":"that the Earth will only last about five billion years"},{"time":52000,"text":"before it's swallowed by the sun."},{"time":55000,"text":"Big events in my life,"},{"time":58000,"text":"a strange child."},{"time":60000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":61000,"text":"Energy, at the moment, is dominated by resource."},{"time":64000,"text":"The countries that make a lot of money out of energy"},{"time":67000,"text":"have something underneath them."},{"time":70000,"text":"Coal-powered industrial revolution in this country --"},{"time":74000,"text":"oil, gas, sorry."},{"time":78000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":81000,"text":"Gas, I'm probably the only person"},{"time":83000,"text":"who really enjoys it when Mister Putin"},{"time":85000,"text":"turns off the gas tap, because my budget goes up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":88000,"text":"We're really dominated now"},{"time":93000,"text":"by those things that we're using up faster and faster and faster."},{"time":98000,"text":"And as we try to lift billions of people out of poverty"},{"time":101000,"text":"in the Third World, in the developing world,"},{"time":105000,"text":"we're using energy faster and faster."},{"time":107000,"text":"And those resources are going away."},{"time":109000,"text":"And the way we'll make energy in the future"},{"time":111000,"text":"is not from resource,"},{"time":114000,"text":"it's really from knowledge."},{"time":116000,"text":"If you look 50 years into the future,"},{"time":119000,"text":"the way we probably will be making energy"},{"time":121000,"text":"is probably one of these three,"},{"time":124000,"text":"with some wind, with some other things,"},{"time":126000,"text":"but these are going to be the base load energy drivers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":129000,"text":"Solar can do it, and we certainly have to develop solar."},{"time":134000,"text":"But we have a lot of knowledge to gain before we can make solar"},{"time":137000,"text":"the base load energy supply for the world."},{"time":141000,"text":"Fission."},{"time":144000,"text":"Our government is going to put in six new nuclear power stations."},{"time":148000,"text":"They're going to put in six new nuclear power stations,"},{"time":150000,"text":"and probably more after that."},{"time":152000,"text":"China is building nuclear power stations. Everybody is."},{"time":154000,"text":"Because they know that that is one sure way"},{"time":157000,"text":"to do carbon-free energy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161000,"text":"But if you wanted to know what the perfect energy source is,"},{"time":164000,"text":"the perfect energy source is one"},{"time":166000,"text":"that doesn't take up much space,"},{"time":169000,"text":"has a virtually inexhaustible supply,"},{"time":172000,"text":"is safe, doesn't put any carbon into the atmosphere,"},{"time":176000,"text":"doesn't leave any long-lived radioactive waste:"},{"time":180000,"text":"it's fusion."},{"time":182000,"text":"But there is a catch. Of course there is always a catch in these cases."},{"time":184000,"text":"Fusion is very hard to do."},{"time":187000,"text":"We've been trying for 50 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":190000,"text":"Okay. What is fusion? Here comes the nuclear physics."},{"time":193000,"text":"And sorry about that, but this is what turns me on."},{"time":196000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":198000,"text":"I was a strange child."},{"time":202000,"text":"Nuclear energy comes for a simple reason."},{"time":206000,"text":"The most stable nucleus is iron, right in the middle of the periodic table."},{"time":210000,"text":"It's a medium-sized nucleus."},{"time":212000,"text":"And you want to go towards iron if you want to get energy."},{"time":216000,"text":"So, uranium, which is very big, wants to split."},{"time":219000,"text":"But small atoms want to join together,"},{"time":222000,"text":"small nuclei want to join together"},{"time":224000,"text":"to make bigger ones to go towards iron."}]},{"cues":[{"time":226000,"text":"And you can get energy out this way."},{"time":228000,"text":"And indeed that's exactly what stars do."},{"time":230000,"text":"In the middle of stars, you're joining hydrogen together to make helium"},{"time":234000,"text":"and then helium together to make carbon,"},{"time":236000,"text":"to make oxygen, all the things that you're made of"},{"time":238000,"text":"are made in the middle of stars."},{"time":241000,"text":"But it's a hard process to do"},{"time":243000,"text":"because, as you know, the middle of a star is quite hot,"},{"time":246000,"text":"almost by definition."},{"time":250000,"text":"And there is one reaction"},{"time":253000,"text":"that's probably the easiest fusion reaction to do."},{"time":258000,"text":"It's between two isotopes of hydrogen, two kinds of hydrogen:"},{"time":262000,"text":"deuterium, which is heavy hydrogen,"},{"time":265000,"text":"which you can get from seawater,"},{"time":267000,"text":"and tritium which is super-heavy hydrogen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":271000,"text":"These two nuclei, when they're far apart, are charged."},{"time":275000,"text":"And you push them together and they repel."},{"time":278000,"text":"But when you get them close enough,"},{"time":280000,"text":"something called the strong force starts to act"},{"time":282000,"text":"and pulls them together."},{"time":284000,"text":"So, most of the time they repel."},{"time":286000,"text":"You get them closer and closer and closer and then at some point"},{"time":288000,"text":"the strong force grips them together."},{"time":291000,"text":"For a moment they become helium 5,"},{"time":293000,"text":"because they've got five particles inside them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":295000,"text":"So, that's that process there. Deuterium and tritium goes together"},{"time":297000,"text":"makes helium 5."},{"time":299000,"text":"Helium splits out, and a neutron comes out"},{"time":302000,"text":"and lots of energy comes out."},{"time":304000,"text":"If you can get something to about 150 million degrees,"},{"time":307000,"text":"things will be rattling around so fast"},{"time":309000,"text":"that every time they collide in just the right configuration,"},{"time":313000,"text":"this will happen, and it will release energy."},{"time":315000,"text":"And that energy is what powers fusion."},{"time":319000,"text":"And it's this reaction that we want to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":322000,"text":"There is one trickiness about this reaction."},{"time":325000,"text":"Well, there is a trickiness that you have to make it 150 million degrees,"},{"time":328000,"text":"but there is a trickiness about the reaction yet."},{"time":331000,"text":"It's pretty hot."},{"time":333000,"text":"The trickiness about the reaction is that"},{"time":335000,"text":"tritium doesn't exist in nature."},{"time":337000,"text":"You have to make it from something else."},{"time":339000,"text":"And you make if from lithium. That reaction at the bottom,"},{"time":342000,"text":"that's lithium 6, plus a neutron,"},{"time":346000,"text":"will give you more helium, plus tritium."},{"time":348000,"text":"And that's the way you make your tritium."},{"time":350000,"text":"But fortunately, if you can do this fusion reaction,"},{"time":353000,"text":"you've got a neutron, so you can make that happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":357000,"text":"Now, why the hell would we bother to do this?"},{"time":360000,"text":"This is basically why we would bother to do it."},{"time":363000,"text":"If you just plot how much fuel"},{"time":367000,"text":"we've got left, in units of"},{"time":369000,"text":"present world consumption."},{"time":371000,"text":"And as you go across there you see"},{"time":374000,"text":"a few tens of years of oil -- the blue line, by the way,"},{"time":376000,"text":"is the lowest estimate of existing resources."},{"time":379000,"text":"And the yellow line is the most optimistic estimate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":383000,"text":"And as you go across there you will see"},{"time":385000,"text":"that we've got a few tens of years, and perhaps 100 years"},{"time":387000,"text":"of fossil fuels left."},{"time":390000,"text":"And god knows we don't really want to burn all of it,"},{"time":392000,"text":"because it will make an awful lot of carbon in the air."},{"time":394000,"text":"And then we get to uranium."},{"time":397000,"text":"And with current reactor technology"},{"time":399000,"text":"we really don't have very much uranium."},{"time":402000,"text":"And we will have to extract uranium from sea water,"},{"time":404000,"text":"which is the yellow line,"},{"time":406000,"text":"to make conventional nuclear power stations"},{"time":409000,"text":"actually do very much for us."},{"time":411000,"text":"This is a bit shocking, because in fact our government"},{"time":413000,"text":"is relying on that for us to meet Kyoto,"},{"time":416000,"text":"and do all those kind of things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":418000,"text":"To go any further you would have to have breeder technology."},{"time":420000,"text":"And breeder technology is fast breeders. And that's pretty dangerous."},{"time":424000,"text":"The big thing, on the right,"},{"time":426000,"text":"is the lithium we have in the world."},{"time":428000,"text":"And lithium is in sea water. That's the yellow line."},{"time":431000,"text":"And we have 30 million years worth of fusion fuel in sea water."},{"time":435000,"text":"Everybody can get it. That's why we want to do fusion."},{"time":438000,"text":"Is it cost-competitive?"},{"time":441000,"text":"We make estimates of what we think it would cost"},{"time":443000,"text":"to actually make a fusion power plant."},{"time":445000,"text":"And we get within about the same price"},{"time":448000,"text":"as current electricity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":450000,"text":"So, how would we make it?"},{"time":452000,"text":"We have to hold something at 150 million degrees."},{"time":455000,"text":"And, in fact, we've done this."},{"time":458000,"text":"We hold it with a magnetic field."},{"time":460000,"text":"And inside it, right in the middle of this toroidal shape, doughnut shape,"},{"time":465000,"text":"right in the middle is 150 million degrees."},{"time":467000,"text":"It boils away in the middle at 150 million degrees."},{"time":471000,"text":"And in fact we can make fusion happen."},{"time":473000,"text":"And just down the road, this is JET."},{"time":475000,"text":"It's the only machine in the world that's actually done fusion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":477000,"text":"When people say fusion is 30 years away, and always will be,"},{"time":480000,"text":"I say, \"Yeah, but we've actually done it.\" Right?"},{"time":483000,"text":"We can do fusion. In the center of this device"},{"time":485000,"text":"we made 16 megawatts of fusion power in 1997."},{"time":488000,"text":"And in 2013 we're going to fire it up again"},{"time":491000,"text":"and break all those records."},{"time":493000,"text":"But that's not really fusion power. That's just making some fusion happen."},{"time":496000,"text":"We've got to take that, we've got to make that into a fusion reactor."},{"time":499000,"text":"Because we want 30 million years worth of fusion power for the Earth."},{"time":504000,"text":"This is the device we're building now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":506000,"text":"It gets very expensive to do this research."},{"time":508000,"text":"It turns out you can't do fusion on a table top"},{"time":510000,"text":"despite all that cold fusion nonsense. Right?"},{"time":513000,"text":"You can't. You have to do it in a very big device."},{"time":516000,"text":"More than half the world's population is involved in building this device"},{"time":519000,"text":"in southern France, which is a nice place to put an experiment."},{"time":522000,"text":"Seven nations are involved in building this."},{"time":526000,"text":"It's going to cost us 10 billion. And we'll produce half a gigawatt of fusion power."},{"time":530000,"text":"But that's not electricity yet."},{"time":533000,"text":"We have to get to this."},{"time":535000,"text":"We have to get to a power plant."},{"time":537000,"text":"We have to start putting electricity on the grid"},{"time":539000,"text":"in this very complex technology."},{"time":541000,"text":"And I'd really like it to happen a lot faster than it is."},{"time":544000,"text":"But at the moment, all we can imagine is sometime in the 2030s."}]},{"cues":[{"time":549000,"text":"I wish this were different. We really need it now."},{"time":551000,"text":"We're going to have a problem with power"},{"time":553000,"text":"in the next five years in this country."},{"time":555000,"text":"So 2030 looks like an infinity away."},{"time":559000,"text":"But we can't abandon it now; we have to push forward,"},{"time":561000,"text":"get fusion to happen."},{"time":563000,"text":"I wish we had more money, I wish we had more resources."},{"time":565000,"text":"But this is what we're aiming at,"},{"time":567000,"text":"sometime in the 2030s --"},{"time":569000,"text":"real electric power from fusion. Thank you very much."},{"time":571000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}